Before your interview remember to memorise the answers to all the possible questions that the interviewer might ask you. My friend Charles speaks four languages fluently. He told me "because it has a jargonistic tone, instead of writing as per our previous conversation you can simply write as we discussed or as discussed. Instead of writing as per your request we can just write as you requested. Rather than say as per our agreement we can simply say as we agreed. Rather than say please find attached the receipt, we can just say attached is the receipt. Instead of saying I enclose herewith two documents it's more natural to say enclosed are two documents or I've enclosed two documents. Instead of saying here is the report for your perusal, it's more natural to say here is the report for your review. Instead of saying please return the form at your earliest convenience, we can say please return the form by next week." Charles is a boxing fan. Channel two gives in-depth coverage of boxing fights. John's fight with Dan got wide media coverage. His match with Alexander also received detailed press coverage. He tends to get lots of newspaper and magazine coverage as his fights are exciting to watch. The organisation is gonna hold an election for the chairman tomorrow channel two will give the election extensive coverage. Of you wanna check out the reports of John's previous fights their monthly magazines have extensive coverage of them. The book "martial arts techniques" provide good grappling techniques coverage. By the way Japan Mobile now has nationwide coverage with its network. Their network coverage used to be poor in osaka which affected how people could access the internet but now it's considered one of the best. Their coverage is fantastic throughout the country. Charles is a basoonist. He's looking at a few insurance plans and choosing one that provides the most adequate life medical and health insurance cover. He's thinking of paying an additional premium to have insurance coverage for accidental damage to his bassoon as well as increasing the cover up to a million yen. Do you believe in horoscope? What zodiac sign are you? To me the personality description at times seems correct but I don't believe in the foretelling. I'm a Leo. Tell me about the disposition and personality traits typical of a Leo. I want to see if they're accurate. Are you into meditation as well? Today many people practise zen meditation in pursuit of tranquility and happiness. Charles' cousin has her oboe exam next week. She wants him to accompany her free of charge. He isn't sure if he wants to do it but he doesn't want her to feel like the rug is bring pulled out from under her. Charles honours his parents and is thankful for what they've done for him. His sister is also a good daughter while his brother needs to be a better son. In the east teachers and parents stress the importance of filial piety which means chinese parental respect. They teach that you should honour your parents and take care of them. Recently charles' cousin has stolen his watchband. It became a.matter of honour to tell him about it. My brother too felt honour bound to tell him. His dad is a man of honor and great integrity. Charles and I are kickboxing fans. In march Fred will be fighting joe for the heavyweight title for the honour of his country. Winning it is a matter of personal honour, family honour and national honour. Recently his church held a feast in honour of Fred. Charles asked me if I would do him the honour of accompanying him to the feast which I did. It was a great honour to see him. When he saw us he said humbly "it's a signal honour to have you here charles" We asked him if he would do us the honour of being our grappling coach. He said "we'll have to see" A couple waiters did the honours and greeted the guests at the door. After we sat down Fred said to a waitress "will you do the honours and cut us a piece of chicken?"
